  <front>
    <title>Deprecating gmt_unix_time in TLS</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-mathewson-no-gmtunixtime-00"/>
    <author initials="N." surname="Mathewson" fullname="Nick Mathewson">
      <organization>Tor</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="B." surname="Laurie" fullname="Ben Laurie">
      <organization>Google</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="05" month="December" year="2013"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   This memo deprecates the use of the gmt_unix_time field for sending
   the current time in all versions of the TLS protocol's handshake.  A
   rationale is provided for this decision, and alternatives are
   discussed.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
